headline.main: SUDAN UNITS SEIZE A TOWN IN ETHIOPIA; Capture 515 Prisoners -- Haile Selassie Expected to Enter Addis Ababa Tomorrow AXIS IS STALLED IN NORTH Its Force in Egypt Hampered by Sandstorm and British Harassing Activities

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, April 30 -- While activities on the Libyan-Egyptian front were confined to patrol activities, British troops pushed ahead on various East African fronts. A force that had been moving southward toward Dessye, Ethiopia, left the main road from Asmara to Dessye and captured the Italian post of Socota last Sunday.
